# Medical Store Blueprint

Use this rule for all generated code in this project.

## Project Architecture

Enforce this folder structure:

```txt
src/
  app/
    pages/
      HomePage.tsx
      ListingPage.tsx
      DetailPage.tsx
      CartPage.tsx
      CheckoutPage.tsx
      ConfirmationPage.tsx
      LoginPage.tsx
      AccountPage.tsx
      admin/
        AdminDashboardPage.tsx
        AdminProductsPage.tsx
        AdminOrdersPage.tsx
        AdminCustomersPage.tsx
        AdminSettingsPage.tsx
  components/
    common/
    layout/
    product/
    cart/
    checkout/
    account/
    admin/
  context/
    AuthContext.tsx
    CartContext.tsx
    ProductContext.tsx
  data/
    products.ts
    categories.ts
    users.ts
  hooks/
    useAuth.ts
    useCart.ts
    useLocalStorage.ts
    useProducts.ts
  routes/
    AppRoutes.tsx
    ProtectedRoute.tsx
    AdminRoute.tsx
  utils/
    currency.ts
    date.ts
    validation.ts
    order.ts
  types/
    models.ts
```

File placement rules:
- New page: `src/app/pages/**`
- New reusable UI: `src/components/**`
- New global state: `src/context/**`
- New static/seed/mock data: `src/data/**`
- New custom hook: `src/hooks/**`
- New route logic: `src/routes/**`
- New pure helper: `src/utils/**`
- New TS models/interfaces: `src/types/**`

## Data Models (TypeScript)

All model types must live in `src/types/models.ts` and be imported everywhere:

```ts
export type Product = {
  id: string;
  slug: string;
  sku: string;
  name: string;
  category: 'mobility' | 'monitoring' | 'respiratory' | 'diagnostics' | 'rehab' | 'consumables';
  brand: string;
  shortDescription: string;
  description: string;
  price: number;
  stock: number;
  requiresPrescription: boolean;
  imageUrl: string;
  rating: number;
  reviewCount: number;
  certifications: ('FDA' | 'CE')[];
};

export type CartItem = {
  productId: string;
  name: string;
  unitPrice: number;
  quantity: number;
  imageUrl: string;
  requiresPrescription: boolean;
};

export type Customer = {
  id: string;
  firstName: string;
  lastName: string;
  email: string;
  phone: string;
  defaultAddress?: string;
  isAdmin: boolean;
};

export type Order = {
  id: string;
  customerId: string;
  items: CartItem[];
  subtotal: number;
  shipping: number;
  tax: number;
  total: number;
  status: 'pending' | 'paid' | 'processing' | 'shipped' | 'delivered' | 'cancelled';
  paymentMethod: 'cod' | 'card';
  prescriptionAcknowledged: boolean;
  createdAt: string;
};
```

## Page Feature Specs

- `HomePage`: hero, category cards, featured products, trust strip (FDA/CE badges, secure checkout, support).
- `ListingPage`: category filter, search, sort, product grid, pagination, low-stock label.
- `DetailPage`: gallery, certifications, price, stock, quantity picker, add-to-cart, prescription warning if needed.
- `CartPage`: line items, quantity update, remove, subtotal/tax/total summary, continue shopping, checkout CTA.
- `CheckoutPage`: customer form, shipping summary, payment selector, prescription acknowledgment checkbox, place-order action.
- `ConfirmationPage`: order number, ordered items, totals, shipping details, next-step guidance.
- `LoginPage`: email/password form, validation, role-aware redirect (customer/admin).
- `AccountPage`: profile summary, order history list, order status badges.
- Admin panel pages:
- `AdminDashboardPage`: KPI cards (orders, revenue, customers, low stock), recent orders.
- `AdminProductsPage`: list/create/edit products, stock and prescription flags.
- `AdminOrdersPage`: order table, status update actions, detail preview.
- `AdminCustomersPage`: customer list and profile preview.
- `AdminSettingsPage`: business info, shipping/tax defaults, policy text blocks.

## State Rules

- Use React `useState` as default state primitive.
- Use Context only for global state (`auth`, `cart`, `products`).
- Persist `cart` and `auth` snapshot in `localStorage`.
- No prop drilling deeper than 2 levels; extract component or use context before that.
- Keep page-specific UI state local to page/component.
- No external state library (Redux, Zustand, MobX, Recoil, etc.).

## Tailwind Design System

Use this palette and token intent:
- `primary-50..900`: blue scale for brand, headings, key actions.
- `accent-50..900`: teal scale for highlights and positive indicators.
- `neutral-50..900`: backgrounds, borders, body text.
- `success`, `warning`, `error`: semantic feedback colors.

Style rules:
- Spacing follows Tailwind scale (`2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16` etc.); do not invent random pixel spacing.
- Radius: `rounded-lg` for controls/cards, `rounded-2xl` for hero/feature blocks.
- Shadows: subtle medical-professional depth only (`shadow-sm`, `shadow-md`).
- Breakpoints must use Tailwind defaults (`sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`) with mobile-first layouts.

## Medical UX Rules

- Always show trust signals in product and checkout flows (FDA/CE badges where applicable).
- For `requiresPrescription` items, show warning banner on product detail, cart, and checkout.
- Copy tone: professional, clear, safety-first; avoid hype or slang.
- Include support and returns reassurance on conversion-critical pages.
- Use accessible language, clear form labels, and actionable error messages.

## Hard Constraints

- No UI component libraries (MUI, Ant, Chakra, shadcn, etc.).
- No backend/server/API generation in this project.
- No inline styles; use Tailwind utility classes only.
- No React class components; functional components only.
- Keep dependencies minimal and stack-consistent.

## Seed Data Spec

Provide at least 12 products in `src/data/products.ts` across 6 categories (minimum 2 each):
- Mobility
- Monitoring
- Respiratory
- Diagnostics
- Rehab
- Consumables

Each seed product must include:
- valid `id`, `slug`, `sku`
- realistic medical naming and pricing
- stock count
- at least one certification tag (`FDA` or `CE`)
- `requiresPrescription` flag where clinically appropriate
